The paper focuses on developing a unified mobile search framework, which involves analyzing search queries and user behaviors, and proposing neural models for target app selection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with user engagement and behavior, which falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The proposed neural models also involve learning high-dimensional representations, which is a common theme in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
